</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>In words:
An update (installing in the user repository) is possible, if
</p>
<ol><li>there is shared extension (no user) and the bundled or online repository contains a higher version</li>
<li>there is a user extension and the shared, bundled or online repository contains a higher version</li></ol>
<p>The next table shows the case where the user has <b>write permission</b> in the shared folder. In all those cases the update/installation will happen in the <b>shared repository</b>. If a user extension exists does not matter.
</p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="2">
<tbody><tr>
<th>
</th>
