<h4><span id="Element_.2Fdescription.2Fdependencies.2FOpenOffice.org-minimal-version"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Element_/description/dependencies/OpenOffice.org-minimal-version">Element <code class="language-none">/description/dependencies/OpenOffice.org-minimal-version</code></span></h4>
<ul><li>Parent: <code class="language-none">&lt;dependencies&gt;</code></li>
<li>Children: none</li>
<li>Since: OpenOffice.org 2.1</li></ul>
<table border="1" cellpadding="4" style="border-collapse:collapse;">

<caption>Attributes of <code class="language-none">&lt;OpenOffice.org-minimal-version&gt;</code>
</caption>
<tbody><tr bgcolor="#EDEDED">
<th>Attribute
</th>
<th>Description
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td><code class="language-none">xmlns:d</code>
</td>
<td>The namespace for dependency information (inherited from <code class="language-none">&lt;description&gt;</code>) must be defined as
<p><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://openoffice.org/extensions/description/2006">http://openoffice.org/extensions/description/2006</a>
</p>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><code class="language-none">d:name</code>
</td>
<td>Required. Descriptive string that will be displayed. Example&nbsp;: ŌĆ£LibreOffice valueŌĆØ (where value is the value of the attribute value).
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><code class="language-none">d:OpenOffice.org-minimal-version</code>
</td>
<td>Optional. This attribute should never be used with this element.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><code class="language-none">value</code>
</td>
<td>Required. String. The required underlying software version (ŌĆ£2.1ŌĆØ, ŌĆ£2.2ŌĆØ, etc.), starting with OpenOffice.org 2.1. You should not specify a particular micro version, e.g. ŌĆ£2.2.1ŌĆØ, use ŌĆ£2.2ŌĆØ instead.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>See also</b>
</p>
